	<description>
	Havre is a first person exploration game set in a forsaken cylindrical world.
	Despite its apparent lifelessness this world was once built to be an artificial haven.
	Players can progressively reawaken the world through activating its inner mechanisms for 
	creating wind, heat and light.
	</description>
	
	<history>
	Havre started as the game around which Le Chant du cygne collective was created. At first, Havre 
	was centered around a sight mechanic inspired by Tarkovsky's Solaris. But, since the game took place
	in a giant cylindrical world offering so many possibilities it quickly became the main focus of the game.
	The sight mechanic was then delayed to a future game based on procedural mesh deformation.
	</history>

	<features>
		<feature>First person exploration of a cylindrical world.</feature>
		<feature>Night and day cycles, weather and gravity simulation of a cylindrical world.</feature>
		<feature>Dozens of ways to reawaken the world.</feature>
		<feature>Multiple paythrough possibles.</feature>
	</features>
	
